f=Brand Studio/kai/custom/brand-context/SKILL.md · in=brand-context kai's ground-truth layer: one maintained file brand holding *analytical* facts audience definition, positioning, business model mechanics, KPI baselines dates, seasonality notes analysis loads before answering anything. blueprint's context/ pattern applied analytics: answer documented baselines, update them cadence, never let "what's normal brand" live memory. · p=Analysis without documented baselines produces confident nonsense: "traffic spike" that's seasonality, "CAC problem" measured against number nobody wrote down, comparisons across brands different models. context file makes kai answer auditable *this* number, against *that* documented baseline, *this* date. · wu=Triggers: "[brand] performance," "[brand] audience," "what's normal [brand]," creating/updating brand's context file automatically load step kai analysis (dashboards, funnels handed nate, SEO context). · st:/ Protocol=`Load the brand's context file (config path) \· -> If none: BUILD it with the operator (template; real facts + instrumented baselines only) \· -> Answer analyses FROM documented baselines (cited, dated) \· -> Monthly baseline refresh: instrumented actuals in, stale entries re-dated, \· changes logged (append-only)` · h3:Phase Build (once brand)=operator, real sources: audience (who actually buys data/interviews, aspiration), positioning (one paragraph, consistent weave's arc echo's narrative contradictions between three finding), model mechanics (how money actually flows: AOV, purchase frequency, margin shape operator-supplied), KPI baselines (only instrumented numbers, dated source), seasonality/context notes. **No invented baselines**: unmeasured KPI listed "not instrumented," routed instrumentation queue. · h3:Phase Load Answer=kai analysis opens relevant context file answers against it: "signups 22% over documented baseline (340/wk, June)" never bare numbers against remembered normals. Multi-brand operators get per-brand answers; cross-brand comparisons state model differences before comparing anything. · h3:Phase 3 — Maintain=Monthly (config cadence): actuals refresh baselines (old value new value, logged append-only), stale entries (older cadence) get re-confirmed flagged, file-vs-reality contradictions escalate operator blueprint's contradiction-audit habit, applied numbers layer. · of=Analyses cite: `[metric]: [value] baseline [value] ([date], [source]) [delta]`. file itself follows `assets/brand-context-template.md`. · pr=**Documented baselines "not instrumented" never remembered normals.**, **Every baseline carries date source.** Undated numbers expired (the system-wide dating rule)., **One file brand; comparisons state model differences first.**, **Positioning consistency tripartite** file, weave's arc, echo's narrative contradict; drift between them finding operator., **Append-only updates; contradictions escalate.** · f=context file urgent analysis answer supplied data only, labeled "no baseline context deltas unavailable," start build., Baselines stale beyond cadence answers flag staleness explicitly., Instrumentation gaps routed instrumentation queue (kai's own), never guessed around. · b:with Other Skills=`marketing-dashboards` (sibling) consumes baselines red/green calls; `seo-strategist` (sibling) uses audience/positioning intent work; **nate's** funnel-analysis reads baselines Step-1 context., **atlas/lena/weave** identity/voice/story definitions file holds their *analytical shadow* (who buys, what's claimed), definitions themselves., **echo** consumes baselines investor updates (facts identical, framing echo's)., **The instrumentation queue kai's**, fed agent's blocked-measurement needs.